nodes.bodyText:
I've tried refactoring the code to Either but Either cannot handle a successful call return of a function that returns void
this is needed in situations like
    static CheckedRunnable decorateCheckedRunnable(RateLimiter rateLimiter, int permits,
        CheckedRunnable runnable) {

        return () -> {
            waitForPermission(rateLimiter, permits);
            try {
                runnable.run();
                drainIfNeeded(rateLimiter, CallsResult.success());
            } catch (Exception exception) {
                drainIfNeeded(rateLimiter, CallsResult.failure(exception));
                throw exception;
            }
        };
    }

what should I use here? Either.right(null) ?
and then in the application code which check for a certain condition should I do this:
if (result.isRigth() && result.get() != null) {

?
besides that the API started looking ugly with template mayhem such as:
private final Function<Either<? extends Throwable, Object>, Boolean> drainPermissionsOnResult;

I do not think this is the right approach.
Furthermore where should I put helper methods like isSuccessfulAndReturned:
        RateLimiter limiter = RateLimiter.of("someLimiter", RateLimiterConfig.custom()
            .limitForPeriod(5)
            .limitRefreshPeriod(Duration.ofHours(1))
            .drainPermissionsOnResult(
                callsResult -> callsResult.isSuccessfulAndReturned(
                    ResponseWithOverloadIndication.class,
                    response -> response.isPotentialOverload()))
            .build());

?
